annotationA: F-box and leucine-rich repeat protein 7; Ubiquitin-protein transferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: proximal/distal pattern formation, imaginal disc; SCF-dependent proteasomal ubiquitin-dependent protein catabolic process; regulation of hippo signaling; regulation of protein localization; negative regulation of growth
annotationB: 26S proteasome non-ATPase regulatory subunit 11; Component of the lid subcomplex of the 26S proteasome, a multiprotein complex involved in the ATP-dependent degradation of ubiquitinated proteins. In the complex, RPN6 is required for proteasome assembly (By similarity). May act as linker between 19S regulatory subunit and the 20S proteasome core
